Machine Technology Inc said itexpects to report a second quarter loss of 13 to 17 cts pershare on sales of about 4,400,000 dlrs.    A year earlier, it lost 139,000 dlrs or three cts per shareon sales of 4,271,000 dlrs.    The company said it booked over six mln dlrs in the quarterand its backlog has risen 35 pct since the end of its fiscalyear, leading it to expect improved results in the second half. Reuter&#3;